<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1077203 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2-895x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="855" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2-895x598.jpg 895w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2-487x325.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2-320x214.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2-640x428.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2-600x401.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-2.jpg 922w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Another edition of Baileys BakeFest, Nigeria’s first baking festival took place on December 2nd at Muri Okunola Park, Victoria Island, Lagos. The one-day extravaganza showcased Baileys Delight as the ideal treat while demonstrating the many ways it can be enjoyed. In a three-course contest, the highly anticipated bake-off between four teams of upcoming bakers paired with celebrities lived up to expectations. The three-round contest had participants in their separate booths whipping up tasty pies and tarts, delicious cocktails and the yummiest baked desserts within a given time limit. While teams battled with oven mittens, guests rode the mechanical bull and enjoyed mega Jenga, snakes and ladders and tic-tac-toe. According to one of the guests: “Baileys BakeFest did not just give us yummy pastries and delicious cocktails, we also enjoyed music, fun, and games. It was an all-round treat”. To further make the fest interesting, the finest treat masters from across Nigeria serving up Baileys Delight-infused treats were present. Baileys BakeFest oozed the indulgent lifestyle the brand lives for; From delicious cupcakes to exotic cocktails, Baileys BakeFest had it all! The delicious scent of baked goodies wafted through the park long before the final call was made. The winning team, team TimiKoks dazzled the guests and judges with creatively lavish Baileys Delight-infused presentations that won hearts and taste buds. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1077200 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-897x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="853" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-897x598.jpg 897w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-487x325.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-974x649.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-320x213.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-640x427.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1-600x400.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/BAILEYS-1-1.jpg 1008w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> According to Chef Alex, the grand prize winners stood out for their flair and finesse. Over one million naira was awarded to contestants in cash prizes.